fields.title: Mischka Plain Men T-Shirt
fields.description: T-shirts with bold slogans were popular in the UK in the 1980s. T-shirts were originally worn as undershirts, but are now worn frequently as the only piece of clothing on the top half of the body, other than possibly a brassiere or, rarely, a waistcoat (vest). T-shirts have also become a medium for self-expression and advertising, with any imaginable combination of words, art and photographs on display.
